<h1>Button</h1>

<p>
	The Button control provides a standard button control for use in your web application.  It can have a text title,
	an optional image, an action which is executed upon activation, and supports 2 styles.  Buttons are typically
	added to a <a href="#/content/detail?sectionId=controls&contentId=navbar&title=Navigation%20Bar">Navigation Bar</a>.
</p>

<p>
	The Navigation Bar class will accept a Button as either the leftBarItem or rightBarItem element.  For example, adding a
	Button with the label "Send" to a Navigation Bar:
	<pre><code>myNavigationBar.setRightBarItem(new mui.Button({
    title: 'Send',
    action: function() {
        alert('Clicked send!');
    }
}));</code></pre>
</p>